name: BrightTALK
description: Add an BrightTALK Instance to connect your existing BrightTALK account to the Marketing Hub, allowing you to manage your channels, subscribers, activities, etc. You will need your BrightTALK account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Bulk ignore if email not present
configuration.description: Bulk ignore if email not present

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

resources.description: Find channels in the Marketing Automation system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all channels for a user 386, the search expression parameter will be where=userId = 386.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for channels for userId 24, the search expression will be where=userId>=24. When this parameter is omitted, all channels for the current user are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: Next Page link. You can get this from the Header of the previous search

resources.description: Find activities for a channel in the Marketing Automation system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all contacts whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name like '%data%'. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 200 records will be returned.

parameters.name: channelId
parameters.description: The ID of the channel to find activities from.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for activities for id 24, the search expression will be where=id>=24. When this parameter is omitted, all activities for the current channel are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: Next Page link. You can get this from the Header of the previous search
